      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Cool!  I have not checked anything yet but I think I see what you're trying to do.\nIs the idea to produce a different breakout with the same footprint but different routing for each chip, so that they can be used in the same motherboard?\nMy concern is that from experience so far, non-trivial routing on the CoB breakout is tricky - but I agree at least making clk, rst, UART and (Q)SPI flash match up would be good, and hopefully possible.  After that it would probably just be informed by what makes routing easiest - it doesn't really matter because they are just GPIO pins.",
